                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-27T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. Your 584, March 26, 4 p.m. The denial by Carranza of such true charges
                    constitutes an insult to the Government of the United States, some colleagues
                    and myself. I do not know how you regard it, but as far as I am concerned I
                    would like to be urgently telegraphed the full text of Carranza’s reply or at
                    least the part which contains the criticism against myself. While waiting, what
                    I can assert most emphatically is that the attitude of the Diplomatic Corps here
                    and mine has been during such trying state of things as moderate, true, cautious
                    and loyal to their Governments as that of any similar body in any country under
                    similar conditions if ever any country found itself in such situation, probably
                    unique in the history of the world in modern times.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
